Islington North MP Corbyn has said that the Prime Minister's Question Time is too confrontational in nature and that he will refrain from both witty rhetoric and quips, promising instead to focus on serious issues such as poverty, inequality and the challenges facing young people.
Corbyn has said that Angela Eagle, the shadow government's finance secretary, will substitute for him during Question Time when Corbyn is not attending - for example, when Cameron is abroad.
