In this time of communication through social media, style goes beyond content, and the immediacy of the response is often more important than meaningful contact.
Our digital lives have doubled the need to appear strong, happy, and successful, when in reality, isolation reigns.
This superficial success is dominated by values that psychologists call external: money, image, social status. All this is done at the expense of internal values - inner longing for personal growth and friendship - that have a deeper impact on our mental health.
